logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Environment files — NEVER COMMIT, EVER
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  This rule applies to humans AND automated agents (Lovable, IDE bots,
#  CI workers). If you find yourself with .env staged, STOP. Even values
#  that look "public" (anon keys, project URLs) belong outside the repo so
#  the muscle memory doesn't slip when a real secret needs to live nearby.
#  Real secrets go in Edge Function / GitHub / Vercel / Netlify secret
#  stores — never in a versioned file.
#
#  History note: .env was tracked here in early commits. It carried only
#  Supabase URL + anon JWT (both public-by-design) — no service_role or
#  HMAC secrets ever shipped through it. Audit: 2026-05-17.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Alternative lockfiles — npm is the canonical package manager for this repo.
# Keep package-lock.json only; remove bun.lock(b) / yarn.lock / pnpm-lock.yaml.
bun.lock
bun.lockb
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

